This channel is focused primarily on setting up Linux Mint now. This has always been my dream, but I was scared away by the low amount of views on Linux-related videos. I will do my best to explain step-by-step how to do things. Consider that Windows 10 has NASTY telemetry, and Linux Mint (as of version 19.1) boasts 0% telemetry. I would love to one day only use Linux forever, but I feel that I will always need Windows for something.

Now while that was the original focus of this channel, it also has content about setting up Quake on Linux, GZDoom, Minetest, Openshot, etc. I used to have videos of older copyrighted games (namely Diablo 2 and Borderlands 2) but got scared away because of copyright. description:
Hi, I'm Ben Strader.  
For more than 25 years I've spent my career working in the automotive performance and racing industry from grass roots to NASCAR, Off Road Racing to Powerboats, Reno Racing Airplanes to Land Speed Racing record breaking Motorcycles. 

I was  awarded the SEMA 2018 Engine Builder of the Year award for my work on "Project Spinal Tap", an LS7 engine that ran at over 11,200 rpm and I'm also the winningest Crew Chief in NHRA Factory X with 10 National Event wins and the 2024 Championship to my credit. 

Along the way, I've spent thousands of hours as a professional educator, helping others learn the math and science of high performance engines at EFI University, a school I founded in 2003, and now I've created this YouTube channel as a way of sharing more knowledge with you!

If you're interested in how the pro's design, develop and test world class racing and performance engines then be sure to subscribe and stay tuned for TONS of amazing, free info coming your way!

description:
Imagine what the world would look like if you can stretch a 1 second action in 40 seconds.  To do so require specialized cameras that can shoot a minimum of 1000 frames per second.  Yes, 1000 photographs in a single second.    These photographs are stitched together to create super slow motion video.  

To watch such 1 second events in slow motion expands your mind and I assure you - it will relieve stress as well.  So please slow down with me and watch the videos in its fullest.  

While you will see that the natural world dominates the videos, there will be studio shots as well.

Tryglav is a Croatian one man band band formed in 2018 by Boris Behara. Tired of playing with people who didn’t have his same vision in music, at the beginning of 2018, he started with the idea to create his own band inspired by his love in black metal and horror imaginary. During the year 2018, seven songs have been composed and re-arranged in his personal studio many times before the final versions come out.

Due the poor equipment for vocal recording, vocals had been entrusted to a singer called Morbid according to Behara’s lyrics and patterns. For the live shows and future records, vocals will be recorded by Behara. 
In the year 2019 the album has been finished and the search for a studio for mixing and mastering had started. After many considerations, the studio was chosen, and the album was sent to Emissary Studios in Australia.
Tryglav signed to Extreme Metal Music and premiere the first single "Night Of Whispering Souls" on Antichrist Metalzine in the same year.
